Stock ID*: * "N" refers to lines that were inbred (sib-mated) for at least 5 generations for the DPGP/DPGP2/DPGP3 genomes, and at least 8 generations for the AGES genomes. For the DGRP lines, inbreeding is described in Mackay et al. (2012)
"-1",  "-2" or "-3" refers to extraction lines homozygous for the X, second or third chromosome, respectively. "-1-3" refers to extraction lines homozygous for the X and third chromosomes.
"_1", "_2", etc. refer to DNA library number. Only one library was sequenced for most samples, except where noted in "Comments".
** Total basepair coverage and mean sequencing depth are reported for focal chromosomes only.
Depth is averaged across only sites above quality thresholds.
